claim.claim-text:
1. A method for scaling address space utilization in a multi-threaded, multi-processor computer, the method comprising:
attaching, to process memory of an exporting process, a region of virtual memory specified in a cross-memory descriptor;
requesting, by an importing thread of an importing process having process memory, attachment of the region of virtual memory for exclusive use by the importing thread;
attaching, by an operating system to the process memory of the importing process, the region of virtual memory for exclusive use by the importing thread, thereby creating a lightweight attachment of the region of virtual memory;
requesting, by the importing thread, lightweight detachment of the region of virtual memory from the process memory of the importing process; and
detaching, by the operating system, the region of virtual memory from the process memory of the importing process, including resetting only the segment lookaside buffer of the processor upon which the importing thread runs without resetting other segment lookaside buffers of other processors, thereby effecting a lightweight detachment.

8. A system for scaling address space utilization in a multi-threaded, multi-processor computer, the system comprising:
means for attaching, to process memory of an exporting process, a region of virtual memory specified in a cross-memory descriptor;
means for requesting, by an importing thread of an importing process having process memory, attachment of the region of virtual memory for exclusive use by the importing thread;
means for attaching, by an operating system to the process memory of the importing process, the region of virtual memory for exclusive use by the importing thread;
means for requesting, by the importing thread, lightweight detachment of the region of virtual memory from the process memory of the importing process; and
means for detaching, by the operating system, the region of virtual memory from the process memory of the importing process, including means for resetting only the segment lookaside buffer of the processor upon which the importing thread runs without resetting other segment lookaside buffers of other processors.

15. A computer program product for scaling address space utilization in a multi-threaded, multi-processor computer, the computer program product comprising:
a recording medium;
means, recorded on the recording medium, for attaching, to process memory of an exporting process, a region of virtual memory specified in a cross-memory descriptor;
means, recorded on the recording medium, for requesting, by an importing thread of an importing process having process memory, attachment of the region of virtual memory for exclusive use by the importing thread;
means, recorded on the recording medium, for attaching, by an operating system to the process memory of the importing process, the region of virtual memory for exclusive use by the importing thread;
means, recorded on the recording medium, for requesting, by the importing thread, lightweight detachment of the region of virtual memory from the process memory of the importing process; and
means, recorded on the recording medium, for detaching, by the operating system, the region of virtual memory from the process memory of the importing process, including means, recorded on the recording medium, for resetting only the segment lookaside buffer of the processor upon which the importing thread runs without resetting other segment lookaside buffers of other processors.
